        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer462546074" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5562191619093269008">5++++ stars<br/><br/>This book was not at ALL what I was expecting. Totally blew me AWAY! <br/><br/>Maggie is plugging along in her mundane, boring life - just existing. Then she literally runs into Clayton Reed. Everything changes......<br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380398634i/770635._SY540_.jpg' width='200' height='225' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/> <br/><br/>I love that Maggie was so persistent in pursuing Clay and wasn&apos;t afraid to go for it. <br/><br/>I was instantly connected with Maggie. I was able to relate to her on many levels. She is trying to hold everything together without anyone knowing something is wrong. She is always having to defe</span>
  <span id="freeText5562191619093269008" style="display:none">5++++ stars<br><br>This book was not at ALL what I was expecting. Totally blew me AWAY! <br><br>Maggie is plugging along in her mundane, boring life - just existing. Then she literally runs into Clayton Reed. Everything changes......<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380398634i/770635._SY540_.jpg" width="200" height="225" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br>I love that Maggie was so persistent in pursuing Clay and wasn't afraid to go for it. <br><br>I was instantly connected with Maggie. I was able to relate to her on many levels. She is trying to hold everything together without anyone knowing something is wrong. She is always having to defend her relationship with Clay and keep her friends and family at arms length to keep them from seeing the truth. Maggie thinks she is protecting Clay, but really she is just enabling him.<br><br>This book was so real and raw. I felt every emotion both Maggie and Clay were experiencing. I related to Maggie's decisions, because at her age, that is exactly what I would have done. <br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380398634i/770636.jpg" width="250" height="200" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br><b>This is one of the best books I have read this year</b></span>
  <a data-text-id="5562191619093269008" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

